    ('1961 Ferrari 250 GT California SWB Spider','$17 million', 'https://www.motortrend.com/uploads/sites/11/2015/05/1961-Ferrari-250-GT-SWB-front-three-quarters.jpg?fit=around%7C1000:625','If this car looks familiar, it might be because it’s similar to the one featured in the 1980s hit movie, “Ferris Bueller’s Day Off, reports CNBC. And it’s a gem, as evidenced by the sale of one in 2016 at an auction for $17.16 million. Only about 55 of these were ever made, making this particular model one of the most sought-after Ferraris on the market.','2021-05-07 18:57:42.517205-07');
INSERT INTO main_app_car(name, price, img, description, created_at)
  VALUES
    ('2009 Koenigsegg CCXR Trevita','$4.8 million', 'https://www.supercars.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/2010-koenigsegg-ccxr-trevita-3.jpg','Just when you thought the CCXR couldn’t get any cooler, along comes the limited-edition Trevita. The CCXR Trevita uses white carbon fibers designed to shine like a million diamonds when light hits the car. The fiber was made specifically for this car, of which only two were built in 2009, according to Koenigsegg.This car is so hot that even Floyd Mayweather had to have one.','2021-05-07 18:57:42.517205-07');
