    ('2017 Pagani Huayra BC','$2.75 - 3.25 million', 'https://wallpaperaccess.com/full/2305220.jpg','This auto is an engineering tour de force. And only 20 units were made, according to AutoGuide.com. The carbon fiber used on the bodywork is a unique formula that’s 50 percent lighter than regular carbon fiber. And, it can hit 0 to [approximately] 60 mph in 2.8 seconds.','2021-05-07 18:57:42.517205-07');
INSERT INTO main_app_car(name, price, img, description, created_at)
  VALUES
    ('1954 Oldsmobile F-88','$3.24 million', 'https://c4.wallpaperflare.com/wallpaper/482/68/984/oldsmobile-f-88-concept-wallpaper-preview.jpg','Let’s just say that this is not your father’s Oldsmobile — unless he’s a serious collector. Those looking for rare cars for sale should definitely check out the Oldsmobile F-88. The 1954 Oldsmobile F-88 concept car fetched $3.24 million at auction in 2005. According to a 2005 CNN Money article, this gem has a 324-cubic-inch Oldsmobile Rocket V-8 engine and gets up to 250 horsepower.','2021-05-07 18:57:42.517205-07');
INSERT INTO main_app_car(name, price, img, description, created_at)
  VALUES
    ('1931 Bugatti Type 41 Royale Kellner Coupe','$9.8 million', 'https://investinangra.com/images/2019/SETEMBRO/M/243.jpg','Only three of the six Bugatti Type 41 Royales ever produced were sold, reports CarBuzz. However, because the unbodied chassis cost $30,000 when it was first made during the Great Depression, it’s no surprise that sales were low. In 1987, AP reported that one sold for $9.8 million, which at the time was the highest price ever paid for a car.','2021-05-07 18:57:42.517205-07');
